- **[minor]** The sea being a global unbounded horizontal body is documented as intentional, but combined with cave chambers below sea level it means flooded caves with no water rendering (the visual water is a single plane, per the missing water module's hot-reload hooks) — swim physics in visually dry caves.
- **[minor]** `apply_river_flow` scans every spline segment per body per frame; cache per-entity nearest-segment or skip when far from the river's AABB.
- **Unreviewable:** the entire water *rendering* pipeline (mesh, `WaterMaterial`, shore blending, underwater surface from below) — missing from the dump.

## 9. Player / Physics (`physics_bridge/character.rs`, `body_spec.rs`, `collision_layers.rs`, `motor.rs`, `movement.rs`, `props.rs`)

