# Proposed Fix Order (holistic, dependency-aware)

Each step is scoped to the files we'll touch when you say Continue; I won't chase a green build at the expense of doing these properly.

1. **Terrain pipeline lifecycle** — `pipeline.rs` (+ `residency.rs`, ChunkState in the missing `terrain/mod.rs`, so I'll define the state enum change and you can merge it): add `DensityReady` prefetch state, gate meshing on render radius (kills the annulus churn), enforce `maximum_mesh_jobs`, move trimesh into the async stage and gate on physics radius, `Arc` the edit snapshot, Failed-state retry, O(1) lookups.
2. **Erosion + beach + river trace** — `erosion.rs`, `coast.rs`, `hydrology.rs`: real iterative stream power (recompute slope per iteration), corrected beach profile direction, source-selection and monotonic-water fixes; keep `validate_atlas` in agreement.
3. **Day/night + fog application** — `tweaks.rs` (sun angle/illuminance/color functions), `fog.rs` (apply start distance), `lighting_state.rs`/`celestial.rs` (moon activation, moon direction refresh).
4. **Character controller contact handling** — `character.rs`: rewrite the hit-response cases.
5. **Wetness normalization + geology + material-table dedup** — `surface.rs`, `biome_context.rs`, `materials.rs`.
6. **Water swim-up + dead tweaks** — `water_physics.rs`, `options_panel.rs` (wire or stub-mark), plus `features.rs` regen-staleness fix.
7. **Polish tier** — slot-overflow merge (`chunk_palette.rs`/`surface_nets.rs`), horizon skirt follow/rebuild, hardcoded demo lights/fog volumes, hot-reload no-op systems, `.expect` hardening in camera.